&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The contributions you will make:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position assists regional appraisers in producing high quality appraisals. Obtains and analyzes information or documents and creates work files for both sales and subject properties. Responsible for maintaining accurate data and correcting information as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A typical day:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appraisal Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates an understanding of each County’s Assessor’s on-line system including property identification numbering (tax ID’s) and GIS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviews and interprets legal descriptions and land measurement units to accurately identify the sale or subject property under consideration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Examines plat books and aerial photographs to accurately locate each sale or subject property within the correct township and section.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluates client engagement letters, appraisal requests, and records subject properties in the department&#39;s software tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinates and collaborates with other business units and teams within Compeer, providing support as needed to meet the department&#39;s and organization&#39;s needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivers exceptional service to clients and team members, ensuring a consistent client experience that aligns with Compeer&#39;s mission and vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assembles and binds reports for distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
